==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ovism
<hw>O"vism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ov</ets>um +
<ets>-ism</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The old theory that the
egg contains the whole embryo of the future organism and the germs of
all subsequent offsprings and is merely awakened to activity by the
spermatozoon; -- opposed to <contr>spermism</contr> or
<contr>animalculism</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ovist</ent>⟦br⟧
